  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400\u00b0F (200\u00b0C). Toss chickpeas with olive oil, coriander, cumin, and a pinch of salt; spread on a baking sheet. Roast 20\u201325 minutes, turning halfway, until crunchy.",
    "While chickpeas roast, warm the quinoa on the stove or in the microwave.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk tahini, lemon juice, a splash of water, and a pinch of salt until smooth and pourable.",
    "Toss mixed greens and halved cherry tomatoes in a bowl for the base.",
    "When chickpeas are done, remove from oven and let cool slightly.",
    "Assemble the bowl: layer cooked quinoa, greens, tomatoes, and roasted chickpeas.",
    "Drizzle the tahini dressing evenly over the contents.",
    "Sprinkle roasted pistachios and fresh coriander leaves on top.",
    "Serve immediately, enjoying the crunchy texture and floral aroma."
  ],
